quran[30]{c,v,t}:
  53,33,Observedest thou him who turned away
  53,34,"And gave little, and then stopped"
  53,35,Is with him knowledge of the unseen so that he seeth
  53,36,Hath he not been told of that which is in the writs of Musa
  53,37,And of Ibrahim who faithfully fulfilled
  53,38,"To wit, that a burthened soul shall not bear the burthen of another"
  53,39,And that for man shall be naught save that wherefor he endeavoureth
  53,40,And that his endeavour shall be presently observed
  53,41,Thereafter he shall be recompensed therefor with the fullest recompense
  53,42,And that Unto thy Lord is the goal
  53,43,And that it is He Who causeth to laugh and causeth to weep
  53,44,And that it is He Who causeth to die and causeth to live
  53,45,"And that He createth the pair, the male and the female"
  53,46,From seed when it is emitted
  53,47,And that upon Him is another bringing forth
  53,48,And that it is He Who enricheth and preserveth property
  53,49,And that it is He Who is the Lord of Sirius
  53,50,And that He destroyed the former 'A-ad
  53,51,And that Thamud! He left not
  53,52,And also the people of Nuh aforetime. Verily they were even greater wrong-doers and more contumacious
  53,53,And the subverted cities He overthrew
  53,54,Then covered them with that which covered them
  53,55,Which then of thy Lord's benefits wilt thou doubt
  53,56,This is a warner of the warners of old
  53,57,There hath approached the approaching Hour
  53,58,"None, except Allah, can avert it"
  53,59,At this discourse then marvel ye
  53,60,And laugh and not weep
  53,61,And ye are behaving proudly
  53,62,So prostrate yourselves before Allah and worship